to run front end - 
cd backendJavaSimple; mvn clean compile
mvn exec:java
cd sprBack; mvn spring-boot:run



to build docker image-
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\docker-script-fixed.ps1 build
to run docker image -
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\docker-script-fixed.ps1 run
to stop image - 
docker stop livestock360-backend

# Stop all running containers
docker stop $(docker ps -aq)

# Remove all containers (stopped and running)
docker rm $(docker ps -aq)



Docker Hub Commands:
1. Login to Docker Hub: docker login
2. Tag image: docker tag livestock360-spring-backend:latest abidhasan83/livestock360-spring-backend:latest
3. Push image: docker push abidhasan83/livestock360-spring-backend:latest

Note: You need to create the repository 'livestock360-spring-backend' on Docker Hub first at https://hub.docker.com




